author: RICHARD BROOKS AND BRIAN ROKOS
title: LAKE ELSINORE: Ortega Hwy. wreck kills Orange County motorcyclist (UPDATE 4)
text:
By RICHARD BROOKS AND BRIAN ROKOS / STAFF WRITERS
Published: Oct. 12, 2015 Updated: 9:25 p.m. LAKE ELSINORE: Ortega Hwy. wreck kills Orange County motorcyclist (UPDATE 4) Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Related article Â» A motorcycle wreck killed a 38-year-old Orange County man from Aliso Viejo and closed the Ortega Highway for about three hours above Lake Elsinore, officials say.
Reza Gholamipour died at the scene of the 9:45 a.m. crash in the mountains about three miles west of Grand Avenue, say Riverside County coroner's officials.
The accident also involved a Toyota Tacoma pickup truck and caused a minor injury to a second person, according to California Highway Patrol officers.
